{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17538880","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17538880"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:33:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:33:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16400"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16400","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16400"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.03,0.83,0.05,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9091"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65023"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9091","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9091"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16400"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50459"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2112"},{"type":"tags","id":"4165"},{"type":"tags","id":"4192"},{"type":"tags","id":"4193"},{"type":"tags","id":"4195"},{"type":"tags","id":"4198"},{"type":"tags","id":"4540"},{"type":"tags","id":"4546"},{"type":"tags","id":"4980"},{"type":"tags","id":"10948"},{"type":"tags","id":"10949"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"12802"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21596"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43630"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65023","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65023"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the gynaecology clinic with her partner with concerns about difficulty conceiving. They have been trying to conceive for 3 years with regular unprotected intercourse. She has regular 28-day menstrual cycles. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications except for folic acid supplements. Her partner is 34 years old and healthy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Pelvic examination is unremarkable. Investigations reveal:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnti-M\u00fcllerian hormone: 25 pmol/L (14-30)\u003Cbr /\u003EDay 3 Follicle stimulating hormone: 6 IU/L (3-8)\u003Cbr /\u003EDay 3 Luteinizing hormone: 4 IU/L (2-10)\u003Cbr /\u003EDay 21 Progesterone: 35 nmol/L (\u0026gt;30)\u003Cbr /\u003EHysterosalpingogram: Patent fallopian tubes with normal uterine cavity\u003Cbr /\u003ETransvaginal ultrasound: Normal pelvic anatomy\u003Cbr /\u003EPartner\u0027s semen analysis: Volume 3.5 mL (\u0026gt;1.5), Concentration 55 million/mL (\u0026gt;15), Motility 65% (\u0026gt;40%), Normal morphology 5% (\u0026gt;4%)\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anovulation","Male factor infertility","Unexplained infertility","Diminished ovarian reserve","Tubal factor infertility"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis couple presents with primary infertility, defined as the inability to conceive after 12 months of regular unprotected intercourse. All standard fertility investigations are normal, leading to a diagnosis of \u003Cstrong\u003Eunexplained infertility\u003C/strong\u003E, which accounts for approximately 25-30% of infertility cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnovulation\u003C/strong\u003E is unlikely as the patient has regular menstrual cycles and a normal day 21 progesterone level confirming ovulation. Her gonadotrophin levels are also normal.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMale factor infertility\u003C/strong\u003E is excluded by the normal semen analysis, which shows normal parameters for volume, concentration, motility, and morphology according to World Health Organization criteria.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETubal factor infertility\u003C/strong\u003E has been ruled out by the normal hysterosalpingogram showing patent fallopian tubes and normal uterine cavity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiminished ovarian reserve\u003C/strong\u003E is not present as evidenced by the normal Anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone level and normal day 3 FSH level.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EManagement options for unexplained infertility include expectant management, as spontaneous pregnancy may still occur, or assisted reproductive technologies such as ovulation induction with intrauterine insemination or in vitro fertilisation. The choice depends on factors including the duration of infertility and the couple\u0027s age.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Unexplained infertility is diagnosed when standard fertility investigations are normal in couples who have not conceived after 12 months of regular unprotected intercourse.","Basic fertility investigations should include semen analysis, confirmation of ovulation, and tubal patency assessment.","Anti-M\u00fcllerian hormone levels help assess ovarian reserve and predict response to ovarian stimulation."],"references":["The Unexplained Infertility guideline group, Romualdi D, Ata B, Bhattacharya S, Bosch E, Costello M, Gersak K, Homburg R, Le Clef N, Mincheva M et al. Evidence-based guideline: Unexplained Infertility. 2023. ESHRE, https://www.eshre.eu/guideline/UI."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50459"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16400"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50459","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50459"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-25T12:28:36+10:30","updatedA